> If you are using AMD Radeon or Intel QuickSync instead of the NVIDIA GTX 750, follow these steps to reconfigure the "Zombie" stack:

> Step 1: Run the Swap Script

>Â  * In your terminal, run: nano gpu-swap.sh

>Â  * Paste the script code provided in gpu-swap file.

>Â  * Save and Exit (Ctrl+O, then Ctrl+X).

>Â  * Run it: chmod +x gpu-swap.sh && ./gpu-swap.sh

> Step 2: Edit the Blueprint (docker-compose.yml)

> You must tell the containers to use the system's Direct Rendering Manager (DRM) instead of the NVIDIA Toolkit.

>Â  * Open your config: nano ~/mercury/docker-compose.yml

>Â  * Find the Jellyfin section.

>Â Â Â  3. Delete the lines starting with deploy: and resources:.

>Â Â Â  4. Add these lines exactly under the Jellyfin service name:

> devices:

>Â Â  - /dev/dri:/dev/driÂ  # Maps the GPU to the Zombie

> 

> Step 3: Refresh the Stack

> Run the Mercury reset command to apply the changes:

> m reset

> Step 4: Verify

> Run m gpu to open nvtop. You should now see your AMD or Intel GPU active and ready for transcoding[span_5](end_span)!

